-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----
... paste the Private Key block from Cloudflare here ...
... it will be ~25-30 lines of base64-looking text ...
-----END PRIVATE KEY-----

CRITICAL: This file (origin.key.example) is just a layout reference.
The real key goes in deploy/ssl/origin.key.

The Cloudflare dashboard shows the private key ONCE — at the moment
you create the Origin Certificate. There is no way to retrieve it
later. If you lose it, you must revoke the cert and mint a new one.

Lock down the real origin.key:
  Linux / macOS:   chmod 600 deploy/ssl/origin.key
  Windows:         right-click → Properties → Security → restrict to
                   Administrators + your user only.

NEVER commit origin.key. .gitignore excludes it; if it sneaks in,
revoke the cert in Cloudflare immediately and mint a new one.
